    "ToHeisenberg[expr, {x1, x2, ...} -> {a1, a2, ...}] converts expr written \
in canonical Heisenberg operators x1, x2, ... into an equivalent form in \
terms of the Boson operators a1, a2, ... via a suitable transformation \
between them. ToHeisenberg[expr, x1 -> a1, x2 -> a2, ...] is the same. \
ToHeisenberg[{x1, x2, ...} -> {a1, a2, ...}] or ToHeisenberg[x1 -> a1, x2 -> \
a2, ...] returns a list of replacement rules to be applied later.", 
